-- U.S. Stock Futures Erase Loss; S&P 500 Contract Little Changed
-- Michael P. Regan
-- 2010-07-01T13:05:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/u-s-stock-index-futures-erase-decline-s-p-500-contract-is-little-changed.html

          
          
             U.S. stock-index futures were little
changed, erasing earlier declines triggered by an unexpected
jump in jobless claims and signs that global manufacturing
growth is slowing.  
 Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index futures expiring in September
lost less than 0.1 percent to 1,025.7 at 9:03 a.m. in New York
after reversing a 1 percent slump. Dow Jones Industrial Average
futures rose 2 points, or less than 0.1 percent, to 9,718 after
slumping as much as 71 points earlier.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
